  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and manage a team of Quantity Surveyors in post-contract administration and procurement for fast-track construction projects.</li><li>Oversee project budgeting, cash flow control, cost management, claims processing, contract payments, and final account settlements.</li><li>Review, evaluate, and negotiate subcontractor and supplier quotations, ensuring contract awards align with project budgets and requirements.</li><li>Administer and monitor contractual matters including progress claims, variations, extensions of time (EOT), and loss and expense claims.</li><li>Prepare and present monthly cost and progress reports to support accurate financial tracking and forecasting.</li><li>Liaise closely with clients, consultants, and subcontractors to resolve commercial issues and ensure compliance with contract terms.</li><li>Support contract reviews, procurement strategies, and risk management initiatives.</li><li>Evaluate, certify, and manage subcontractor payments, variation order submissions, and final accounts.</li><li>Drive value engineering and cost optimisation initiatives throughout the project lifecycle.</li><li>Participate in site meetings, audits, and final project handovers relating to commercial and contractual deliverables.</li><li>Maintain accurate and well-organised project documentation.</li></ul><p><strong>What we're looking for : </strong><br /><br />Degree /Diploma in Quantity Surveying, Construction Management, Facilities Management or a related field<br />At least 2-3 years of experience as a Quantity Surveyor in the construction industry<br />Preferred working experience with main contractors in Singapore.<br />Proficiency in cost estimation, project cost management, and contract administration<br />Experience in contract management<br />Attention to detail and methodical approach to work Highly motivated, self-driven with initiatives to work independently.<br />Able to work in a fast paced and dynamic environment<br />Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to liaise with both internal and external stakeholders<br />Strong negotiation, interpersonal skills and a team player<br />Proficient in MS Excel and the ability to learn new specialist software</p>",
